casebody.data:
Paul B. SUCHOW, Respondent,
v.
Margaret SUCHOW, Appellant. Motion No: 2018-406 Court of Appeals of New York. Decided June 7, 2018

***1076On the Court's own motion, appeal dismissed, without costs, upon the ground that the order appealed from does not finally determine the action within the meaning of the Constitution. Motion for leave to appeal dismissed upon the ground that the order sought to be appealed from does not finally determine the action within the meaning of the Constitution.
